Package main.hrn10.docJones

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DocJones
    Implementation of my own DocJones algorithm Given a graph that represents a grid of pillars and connecting planks, finds the shortest path between the bottom right corner of the grid to the top left corner of the grid using only pillars reachable through user designated planks that cross gaps.
    DocJones.Test
    Nested class used for calling private methods from JUnit test cases
    Pillar
    Represents a pillar in the gridded temple used in the DocJones algorithm
    Plank
    Represents a plank (edge) between two pillars (vertexes) in the temple grid used in the DocJones algorithm
    Result
    Represents the result of a recursive call in the DocJones algorithm
